ed as a Cavalry Scout  Infantryman  and Special Forces Weapon Sergeant  First assignment was with the 17th Cavalry Regiment  82d Airborne Division  FT Bragg NC  Sergeant First Class Echevarria has also served with 325th Parachute Infantry Regiment  313th Military Intelligence Battalion of the 82d Airborne Division  14th Military Intelligence Battalion  and 20th Infantry Regiment at FT Lewis WA  7th Special Forces Group  and 1st Special Warfare Training Group  FT Bragg NC  Sergeant First Class Echevarria has served as an Infantry Scout  Cavalry Scout  Infantry and Cavalry Scout Section leader  Long Range Surveillance Team Leader  Scout Platoon Sergeant  Special Forces Weapon Sergeant  Special Forces Operations Sergeant  and Special Forces Qualification Course Chief Instructor  Sergeant First Class Echevarria deployments include several Joint Task Force 6  Plan  Colombia  Country of Colombia  and Operation Enduring Freedom  Afghanistan  Sergeant First Class Echevarria awards and decorations include  Afghanistan Campaign Medal  Joint Service Commendation Medal  Meritorious Service medal  Army Commendation Medal  Army Achievement Medal  Army Superior Unit Award  Army good conduct medal  National Defense Service Medal  Global War On Terrorism Expeditionary Medal  Global War On Terrorism Service Medal  Non Commissioned Officer professional Development Ribbon  Army Service Ribbon  Pathfinder Badge  Master Parachutist Badge  Colombian Master Parachutist Badge  Military Free Fall Master Parachutist Badge  The Expert Infantry Badge  The Combat Infantry Badge  Ranger Tab  and the Special Forces Tab  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 